{
  "masechta": "Meilah",
  "daf": 4,
  "amud": "a-b",
  "macro_segments": [
    {
      "title": "The Status of Me'ilah When Avodah Is Performed with Machshevet Pigul or Other Defects",
      "display_title": "Pigul & Me'ilah Status",
      "timestamp": "00:14",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rav Gidal amar Rav: Zrikat Pigul Does Not Change Me'ilah Status",
          "display_title": "Rav Gidal Zrika Pigul",
          "timestamp": "00:14"
        },
        {
          "title": "Tosafos: Why Zrikat Pigul Is Different from a Regular Zrika—The Principle of Mertzeh L'Pigulo",
          "display_title": "Tosafos Mertzeh",
          "timestamp": "00:24"
        },
        {
          "title": "Pigul Status Exists at Earlier Stages; Yet Zrikat Pigul Cannot Change Me'ilah Without Proper Zrika",
          "display_title": "Pigul Early Stages",
          "timestamp": "01:54"
        },
        {
          "title": "Proof from Braisa: Ha'pigul L'olam Mo'alin Bo—Pigul Never Changes Me'ilah Status",
          "display_title": "Braisa Pigul Me'ilah",
          "timestamp": "02:30"
        },
        {
          "title": "Challenge: Doesn't Even Zrikat Pigul Qualify as a Legitimate Zrika?",
          "display_title": "Challenge Zrika Pigul",
          "timestamp": "03:05"
        },
        {
          "title": "Response: Pigul Zrika Is Not Considered Legitimate; Only Real Zrika Properly Done Changes Status",
          "display_title": "Response Legit Zrika",
          "timestamp": "03:30"
        },
        {
          "title": "Second Braisa Proof: Ha'pigul Bekadshei Kadashim Mo'alin Bo—Pigul by Kodshei Kodashim Retains Me'ilah",
          "display_title": "Braisa Kodshei Kadashim",
          "timestamp": "12:31"
        },
        {
          "title": "Why Not Distinguish Even Within Kodshei Kodashim Before and After Zrika?",
          "display_title": "Before After Zrika",
          "timestamp": "13:46"
        },
        {
          "title": "Conclusion: Zrikat Pigul Is Not Meaningful for Me'ilah Status Change",
          "display_title": "Pigul Not Meaningful",
          "timestamp": "17:00"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "When Does Me'ilah Status Actually Change? The Dispute Between Chizkiya and Rabbi Yochanan",
      "display_title": "Me'ilah Status Change",
      "timestamp": "19:41",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Yehoshua's General Principle: Kol She'yesh Lah She'at Heter L'Kohanim",
          "display_title": "Yehoshua General Rule",
          "timestamp": "19:41"
        },
        {
          "title": "Examples of Meat That Became Fit and Then Defective (She'lanah, Shnitmah, Sheyatzah)",
          "display_title": "Fit Then Defective",
          "timestamp": "20:02"
        },
        {
          "title": "Examples of Meat Never Fit: Shechita with Pigul or Chutz Limkomo",
          "display_title": "Never Fit Pigul",
          "timestamp": "20:26"
        },
        {
          "title": "Bar Kappara Feeds Bar Padda Three Possible Interpretations: Heter Shechita, Heter Zrika, or Heter Achilah",
          "display_title": "Bar Kappara Question",
          "timestamp": "21:08"
        },
        {
          "title": "Chizkiya vs. Rabbi Yochanan Dispute on the Critical Moment for Status Change",
          "display_title": "Chizkiya vs Yochanan",
          "timestamp": "23:25"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Zeira: The Mishnah Is Not Precise to Either Position",
          "display_title": "Zeira Not Precise",
          "timestamp": "23:51"
        },
        {
          "title": "Analysis of Mishnah Lashon: Does It Refer to Meat or Blood Becoming Defective?",
          "display_title": "Meat or Blood",
          "timestamp": "24:14"
        },
        {
          "title": "Reading Veqiblu Pesulim Vezarku Et Dama: One Scenario or Two?",
          "display_title": "Stock Phrase Reading",
          "timestamp": "27:20"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Does a Psul Person's Avodah Make Remaining Blood into Shirayim? Rav Yosef's Challenge",
      "display_title": "Psul Shirayim",
      "timestamp": "29:46",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rav Yosef: Proof from Zevachim About Chatat Psulah—The Principle That Psul Status Doesn't Matter",
          "display_title": "Rav Yosef Zevachim",
          "timestamp": "29:46"
        },
        {
          "title": "Stock Phrase Alert: Kiblu Pesulim Vezarku Appears in Both Meilah and Zevachim Contexts",
          "display_title": "Stock Phrase Alert",
          "timestamp": "32:58"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Assi: Stock Phrase Theory Undermined—Why Use Same Phrase Twice?",
          "display_title": "Rav Assi Objection",
          "timestamp": "36:14"
        },
        {
          "title": "Counter-Explanation: Harav Assi Defends Precise Reading by Explaining Kri'i K'ana Asher Yize Mi-Dammah",
          "display_title": "Kri'i Defense",
          "timestamp": "36:51"
        },
        {
          "title": "Reish Lakish Asks Rabbi Yochanan: Does Psul Make Remaining Blood into Shirayim?",
          "display_title": "Reish Lakish Question",
          "timestamp": "42:22"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Yochanan's Answer: Only Chutz L'Zmano and Chutz L'Mkomo (Pigul) Makes Shirayim",
          "display_title": "Yochanan Pigul Shirayim",
          "timestamp": "42:48"
        },
        {
          "title": "Reasoning: Pigul Is Considered As If Mertzeh Because of the Principle That Pigul Is Accepted in Some Ways",
          "display_title": "Pigul Mertzeh Logic",
          "timestamp": "43:06"
        },
        {
          "title": "Clarification: 'Nothing' Means Nothing of Those Psulim That Are Never Overridden B'Tzibbur",
          "display_title": "Clarification Tzibbur",
          "timestamp": "45:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Exception: Tamei Can Make Shirayim Because Tuma Is Overridden B'Tzibbur (Hutra or D'chuya)",
          "display_title": "Tamei Exception",
          "timestamp": "45:56"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Return to Main Question: Does the Braisa Support That Zrika (Not Kabbalah) Is the Critical Moment?",
      "display_title": "Braisa Zrika Proof",
      "timestamp": "50:13",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Tasha: Ha'pigul L'olam Mo'alin Bo—What Does This Phrase Teach About the Critical Moment?",
          "display_title": "Ha'Pigul L'olam",
          "timestamp": "50:13"
        },
        {
          "title": "Attempted Inference: Braisa Implies That the Critical Moment for Me'ilah Is Kabbalah, Not Later Zrika",
          "display_title": "Inference Kabbalah",
          "timestamp": "50:38"
        },
        {
          "title": "Response: No, You Did Do Zrika—The Defect Was at the Zrika Stage, Not Earlier",
          "display_title": "Did Zrika",
          "timestamp": "51:00"
        },
        {
          "title": "What Does L'olam Add to the Phrase?—Emphasis That Even Zrikat Pigul Does Not Change Status",
          "display_title": "L'olam Emphasis",
          "timestamp": "51:54"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Gidal Amar Rav's Position: Zrikat Pigul Neither Takes Out of Me'ilah Nor Brings Into Me'ilah",
          "display_title": "Rav Gidal Position",
          "timestamp": "53:07"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ongoing Uncertainty: The Precise Definition of the Critical Moment—Shechita, Kabbalah, Zrika, or Achilah",
          "display_title": "Critical Moment Unclear",
          "timestamp": "54:06"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
